{"version":1,"ops":[{"type":5,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1599424594,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOkxhYmVsZWRFdmVudDM3MzQ0NzUzMTQ="},"added":["enhancement"],"removed":[]},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1599480148,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY4ODI4MDM5Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/152#issuecomment-688280396"},"message":"Now I really have to come up with the zero-seed tag. What was the term? Cancelled-out seed?","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1599483694,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY4ODI5MjEwNQ==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/152#issuecomment-688292105"},"message":"I'm not sure what you are talking about... If you mean seed value that zeroes internal seed, it's possible to cancel it out in prvhash, but that won't break the system: there's \"lcg\" and \"Hash\" values available with entropy. But now even when everything is initially zero, it will still work, and will produce good hashes.","files":null},{"type":6,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1599483694,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDE1OlVzZXJDb250ZW50RWRpdElzc3VlQ29tbWVudEVkaXQ6Mzk4MzU0MDI0"},"target":"173579ef51e82a569a30f9a2609e20f69c36191711a89514010028cb1d74da58","message":"I'm not sure what you are talking about... If you mean seed value that zeroes internal seed, it's possible to cancel it out in prvhash, but that won't break the system: there's \"lcg\" and \"Hash\" values available with entropy. But now even when everything is initially zero, it will still work, and will produce adequate hashes (won't pass all the tests, though).","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"1840e3905256ae05a0d1ed3fdecefe41fac4d5a7"},"timestamp":1599483917,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY4ODMxMjg3OA==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/152#issuecomment-688312878"},"message":"It is possible to pass all tests even from zero initial state, but that will require adding some overhead. For now, I think expecting Seed to be zero is enough. Especting InitVec to be zero as well is out of specification.\n\nYou may test zero seed this way:\nmemset( out, 0, 4 );\nuint64_t InitVec[ 2 ] = { 6308131542680191958ULL, 0 };\nprvhash42( (const uint8_t*) key, len, (uint8_t*) out, 4, 0, (uint8_t*) InitVec );","files":null},{"type":3,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1599726101,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDEyOklzc3VlQ29tbWVudDY5MDA3NTY3Ng==","github-url":"https://github.com/rurban/smhasher/issues/152#issuecomment-690075676"},"message":"Done","files":null},{"type":4,"author":{"id":"02a1aba681ab0b039dd509d683ddfb248d3ca047"},"timestamp":1599726101,"metadata":{"github-id":"MDExOkNsb3NlZEV2ZW50Mzc0OTY1ODE0NA=="},"status":2}]}